tee: @jeffstaple
recipe by cozycakes cottage<3

ingredients
for cake:
2 and ¼ cups flour (I use all-purpose flour. King Arthur brand is my favorite)
2 tsp. baking powder
1 tsp. baking soda
2 tsp. cinnamon
1 tsp. ground allspice
¾ tsp. nutmeg
½ tsp. ground ginger
¼ tsp. ground cloves
½ tsp. salt
1 and ⅓ cups canned pumpkin
¾ cup buttermilk
1 tsp. vanilla
1 cup unsalted butter, room temperature
1 cup granulated sugar
¼ cup brown sugar
3 eggs (I use extra-large)

for frosting:
¾ cup unsalted butter, room temperature
8 oz. cream cheese, room temperature
¾ tsp. vanilla
½ tsp. cinnamon
3 cups powdered sugar
1 Tbsp. milk

GUYS. so…i got to collab with nike on this invitation, this call to action, to get us all moving together.

no training necessary, just come move with me on snap, and get to know me a little more on the nike app while you’re at it. be sure to tag me in your videos! can’t wait to see them:)

“move with bailey” filter on snapchat 

snapchat: @baileysok1

@nikewomen @nikelosangeles 
#teamnike #newmoves #ad

dance has given me everything. community, freedom, joy, and honestly, a break from the online noise. i don’t know where I’d be without it, but I do know that i couldn’t be more grateful for it. 

click the link in my bio to learn more about my journey. <3

hair by @amychinbeauty
